    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-02T15:09:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-02T15:09:00-05:00" n="849"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d849">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–154: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d849fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SPJ1"
                            >Sturm</persName> of <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>. Repeated to Paris as telegram 29, to
                        London as telegram 37, and to Saigon as telegram 26.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-02T16:09:00-04:00"
                            >July 2, 1954—4:09 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 511. Reference <gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                        >Secto</gloss>s 517,<note n="2" xml:id="d849fn2">Dated June 24, <ref
                            target="#pg_1233">p. 1233</ref>.</note> 544<note n="3" xml:id="d849fn3"
                        >Dated June 29, <ref target="#pg_1265">p. 1265</ref>.</note> and 549.<note
                        n="4" xml:id="d849fn4">Dated July 1, <ref target="#pg_1266">p.
                        1266</ref>.</note> Have you any further specific information re thinking of
                    various delegations about possible resumption of conference at ministerial
                        level?<note n="5" xml:id="d849fn5">The U.S. Delegation’s reply is contained
                        in telegram <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 556, July 3, <ref
                            target="#pg_1280">p. 1280</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
